msgid "Website style guide"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:6
#: 785ae92306324b63a994276979c7a33c
msgid ""
"This page explains the standards we follow for building and maintaining "
"the website. Please follow these guidelines and conventions when "
"modifying the website. For the standards governing the documentation in "
"particular, please see the :doc:`documentation style guide "
"</developer/general/rst-documentation-style-guide>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:10
#: dd608ea537e243bbacc86e808713419e
msgid "Coding conventions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:12
#: 2f74634d121c4a4388c9733d7ddb3405
msgid ""
"The following conventions apply to the website as a whole, including "
"everything written in HTML, CSS, YAML, and Liquid. These conventions are "
"intended to keep the codebase consistent when multiple collaborators are "
"working on it. They should be understood as a practical set of rules for "
"maintaining order in this specific codebase rather than as a statement of"
" what is objectively right or good."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:15
#: 62539d974d124bc5bdc3dfa53e48d42d
msgid "General practices"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:18
#: 16533221c4b44cffb500057d0131aee0
msgid ""
"Use comments to indicate the purposes of different blocks of code. This "
"makes the file easier to understand and navigate."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:20
#: f52a9f6f7235459788f47a035c22cb90
msgid ""
"Use descriptive variable names. Never use one or two letter variable "
"names. Avoid obscure abbreviations and made-up words."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:22
#: 25e3bcc2ea9642938da2d09047c8be21
msgid ""
"In general, make it easy for others to read your code. Your future self "
"will thank you, and so will your collaborators!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:24
#: 593d9ba5fe1a4be79b4a934706e496ab
msgid ""
"`Don’t Repeat Yourself (DRY)! "
"<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Don%27t_repeat_yourself>`__ Instead of "
"repeating the same block of code multiple times, abstract it out into a "
"separate file and ``include`` that file where you need it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:27
#: 4859e9cf56584efd8f3dfd82d175997b
msgid "Whitespace"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:29
#: f57c04c8c3e94a75bd48d293316c4d9f
msgid "Always use spaces. Never use tabs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:30
#: 3c3ae35af0384dfca35f21e06b7a0192
msgid "Each indentation step should be exactly two (2) spaces."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:31
#: 9435fb2beeda4c5080be00f4e2531484
msgid ""
"Whenever you add an opening tag, indent the following line. (Exception: "
"If you open and close the tag on the same line, do not indent the "
"following line.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:32
#: c809b8f331c94982964a87858a9a861a
msgid "Indent Liquid the same way as HTML."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:33
#: a44f7eaad703491287c08a31d760d737
msgid ""
"In general, the starting columns of every adjacent pair of lines should "
"be no more than two spaces apart (example below)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:34
#: db4e3c2332d84954b9fcaf938a39c991
msgid ""
"No blank or empty lines. (Hint: When you feel you need one, add a comment"
" on that line instead.)"
msgstr ""

