msgid ""
"*Also see* :doc:`How to edit the website </developer/general/how-to-edit-"
"the-website>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:67
#: 1557b523c0e141beb7905206cc99d5c2
msgid ""
"Some of the Qubes OS website pages are stored as plain text Markdown "
"files in the `qubesos.github.io "
"<https://github.com/QubesOS/qubesos.github.io>`__ repository. When making"
" contributions to Markdown files, please observe the following style "
"conventions. If you’re not familiar with Markdown syntax, `this "
"<https://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/>`__ is a great resource."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:71
#: e48b7bc504274c29a8010047aec90b8e
msgid "Hyperlink syntax"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:73
#: e0ef231069c64820b1a4793948e67f7b
msgid ""
"Use non-reference-style links like "
":code:`[website](https://example.com/)`. Do *not* use reference-style "
"links like ``[website][example]``, ``[website][]`` or ``[website]``. This"
" facilitates the localization process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:76
#: b3daf892ff814ab6b72f350fbf23c654
msgid "Relative vs. absolute links"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:78
#: 4dcf512885f04eab8982577568e6d637
msgid ""
"Always use relative rather than absolute paths for internal website "
"links. For example, use ``/donate/`` instead of ``https://www.qubes-"
"os.org/donate/``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:80
#: 2ac1df2912eb4c169559428af8bbfc0a
msgid "You may use absolute URLs in the following cases:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:82
#: 385d5c40e25041ca90dd173df8c9f5f5
msgid "External links"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:83
#: 141ebc56e1164a9da8f4b18a6d7c7087
msgid ""
"URLs that appear inside code blocks (e.g., in comments and document "
"templates, and the plain text reproductions of `QSBs <https://www.qubes-"
"os.org/security/qsb/>`__ and `Canaries <https://www.qubes-"
"os.org/security/canary/>`__), since they’re not hyperlinks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:84
#: 6953be213a074310996681896b26fd4d
msgid ""
"Git repo files like ``README.md`` and ``CONTRIBUTING.md``, since they’re "
"not part of the website itself but rather of the auxiliary infrastructure"
" supporting the website"
msgstr ""

