msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:96
#: 70662719b7644675a562e7be3565ab44
msgid "Image linking"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:98
#: 7d400fa261df49ca9662f945c0a8a074
msgid "To add an image to a page, use the following syntax in the main document."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:104
#: 01c7f4cb6dfa45bd80215a65bf9b3118
msgid ""
"This will make the image a hyperlink to the image file, allowing the "
"reader to click on the image in order to view the full image by itself. "
"This is important. Following best practices, our website has a responsive"
" design, which allows the website to render appropriately across all "
"screen sizes. When viewing this page on a smaller screen, such as on a "
"mobile device, the image will automatically shrink down to fit the "
"screen. If visitors cannot click on the image to view it in full size, "
"then, depending on their device, they may have no way see the details in "
"the image clearly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:106
#: 3b070f5afe3045a59483e15eb7fc043e
msgid ""
"In addition, make sure to link only to images in the `qubes-attachment "
"<https://github.com/QubesOS/qubes-attachment>`__ repository. Do not "
"attempt to link to images hosted on other websites."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:109
#: dc61d70650814dd5b3be0b1c896f99e1
msgid "HTML and CSS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:112
#: da54555850054003a4f5759a567f9968
msgid ""
"Do not write HTML inside Markdown documents (except in rare, unavoidable "
"cases, such as `alerts <#alerts>`__). In particular, never include HTML "
"or CSS for styling, formatting, or white space control. That belongs in "
"the (S)CSS files instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:115
#: a11cc858b34246c3afc616368bb4b235
msgid "Headings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:117
#: d8814cf9d2894564ab6cddac4e2358bd
msgid ""
"Do not use ``h1`` headings (single ``#`` or ``======`` underline). These "
"are automatically generated from the ``title:`` line in the YAML front "
"matter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:119
#: 9e015d70218a4cb080de9b811b046d49
msgid ""
"Use Atx-style syntax for headings: ``##h2``, ``### h3``, etc. Do not use "
"underlining syntax (``-----``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:122
#: 23a86210ec874ae38236707ee64b2b5b
msgid "Indentation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:124
#: 85217b93bd6045b18b53135a9bea9cc8
msgid "Use spaces instead of tabs. Use hanging indentations where appropriate."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:127
#: dcaa40da1d424b7baed3215911b4742c
msgid "Lists"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:129
#: dc1710ad202640a4ab5cdd7864e07256
msgid ""
"If appropriate, make numerals in numbered lists match between Markdown "
"source and HTML output. Some users read the Markdown source directly, and"
" this makes numbered lists easier to follow."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:132
#: ff7be1c7e20b4d168858cc38698cec41
msgid "Code blocks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:134
#: 9f05ed9c55be4e73bd74cbf608b63148
msgid ""
"When writing code blocks, use `syntax highlighting "
"<https://github.github.com/gfm/#info-string>`__ where possible (see `here"
" <https://github.com/jneen/rouge/wiki/List-of-supported-languages-and-"
"lexers>`__ for a list of supported languages). Use ``[...]`` for anything"
" omitted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:137
#: 6d3cc2228a854a4293f90153156741e2
msgid "Line wrapping"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:139
#: ea2d1cd2fdb4460db1b010871551c011
msgid "Do not hard wrap text, except where necessary (e.g., inside code blocks)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:142
#: 4d357808e9cf401ab635619815948876
msgid "Do not use Markdown syntax for styling"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:144
#: 0831fc01d37344cd91face49b76f986e
msgid ""
"For example, there is a common temptation to use block quotations "
"(created by beginning lines with the ``>`` character) in order to "
"stylistically distinguish some portion of text from the rest of the "
"document, e.g.:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:152
#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:171
#: 488fc8837b0443e4b4070d67926bfcbd 9babcc5305634740a80f8cd37d59d921
msgid "This renders as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:154
#: 0e82ae88c07340c3b332cbd1670da73e
msgid "**Note:** This is an important note!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:156
#: 900ecf6d5253432aba4cf87a84a1ec17
msgid "There are two problems with this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:158
#: d0b868ff4f4748c491c5af873e355a36
msgid ""
"It is a violation of the `separation of content and presentation "
"<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Separation_of_content_and_presentation>`__,"
" since it abuses markup syntax in order to achieve unintended stylistic "
"results. The Markdown (and HTML, if any) should embody the *content* of "
"the documentation, while the *presentation* is handled by (S)CSS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:160
#: 58c9612e11dd412085ccc5ad3ae4bf2a
msgid ""
"It is an abuse of quotation syntax for text that is not actually a "
"quotation. (You are not quoting anyone here. You’re just telling the "
"reader to note something and trying to draw their attention to your note "
"visually.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/general/website-style-guide.rst:164
#: 58e2b5dbb7794302b93be64323dd0d95
msgid ""
"Instead, an example of an appropriate way to stylistically distinguish a "
"portion of text is by using `alerts <#alerts>`__. Consider also that "
"extra styling and visual distinction may not even be necessary. In most "
"cases, traditional writing methods are perfectly sufficient, e.g.,:"
msgstr ""

